"font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">he ESF has supported polic</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ies targeted</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> at unemployed young people in a variety of ways.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The main types of polici</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">es can be summarised as those</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> that are aimed at preventing early school leaving.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">There are some successful examples like the second-chance schools across Europe</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and in </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">France</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> in particular</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> that has</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> very good reintegration rates.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">there is concern even from the C</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">ommission that the availability of data</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> and</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> monitoring needs to be improved for the policies that target early school leaving.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">Also we need to know more, even after